      void clear()

      void insert(java.lang.Object o)
      resizes the array to a size double the length of the original, inserts the object in the argument into the array above the element that rear points to, and increments count and rear by 1
      boolean isEmpty()
      returns true if the count equals 0, the count decrements when an item is removed but increments when an item is inserted
      boolean isFull()
      returns true the count equals the length of the array that the object queue is implemented by.the count decrements when an item is removed but increments when an item is inserted
      java.lang.Object query()
      returns the item at the front of the queue, or the item that will be removed next, if the queue is not empty
      java.lang.Object remove()
      removes the object in the array at the element that front points to, then increments front, and decrements count by 1
